{"parse":{"title":"Video lesson","pageid":33130335,"revid":854708566,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>A <b>video lesson</b> or <b>lecture</b> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Video\" title=\"Video\">video</a> which presents educational material for a topic which is to be learned.  \n</p><p>The format may vary.  It might be a video of a teacher speaking to the camera, photographs and text about the topic or some mixture of these.  The <a href=\"/wiki/Khan_Academy\" title=\"Khan Academy\">Khan Academy</a> has been successful in teaching mathematics using notes written using <a href=\"/wiki/Yahoo!\" title=\"Yahoo!\">Yahoo!</a>'s doodle pad with a voiceover by <a href=\"/wiki/Salman_Khan_(educator)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Salman Khan (educator)\">Salman Khan (educator)</a>.  These were then loaded onto <a href=\"/wiki/YouTube\" title=\"YouTube\">YouTube</a> where they have been popular and influential.  Such lectures are a key part of <a href=\"/wiki/Flip_teaching\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Flip teaching\">flip teaching</a> in which the initial work of communicating the essentials of the topic is done by the video lesson.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Video_lesson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Lecture\" title=\"Lecture\">Lecture</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Lesson\" title=\"Lesson\">Lesson</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Video_lesson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.economist.com/node/21529062\">\"Flipping the classroom\"</a>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Economist\" title=\"The Economist\">The Economist</a></i>, 17 Sep 2011</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Economist&amp;rft.atitle=Flipping+the+classroom&amp;rft.date=2011-09-17&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Fnode%2F21529062&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AVideo+lesson\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFDiana_Mehta2011\" class=\"citation\">Diana Mehta (8 Sep 2011), <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/technology/digital-culture/social-networking/video-in-the-class-keeps-savvy-students-engaged/article2157948/\">\"Video in the class keeps savvy students engaged\"</a>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Canadian_Press\" title=\"The Canadian Press\">The Canadian Press</a></i></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Canadian+Press&amp;rft.atitle=Video+in+the+class+keeps+savvy+students+engaged&amp;rft.date=2011-09-08&amp;rft.au=Diana+Mehta&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theglobeandmail.com%2Fnews%2Ftechnolog